article.description: Pierre Pierce scored 17 points to go with five assists and four steals and Iowa spoiled the return of former coach Tom Davis with a 74-56 victory over Drake on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Davis has scrappy Drake team
article.linkText: Dr. Tom's return to Iowa spoiled by Hawks
article.story: IOWA CITY, Iowa (AP) -- Pierre Pierce scored 17 points to go with five assists and four steals and Iowa spoiled the return of former coach Tom Davis with a 74-56 victory over Drake on Tuesday night. Jared Reiner and Greg Brunner each scored 13 points for the Hawkeyes (2-0), who started the second half with a 25-9 run to break it open and beat Drake (1-1) for the 25th straight time. Davis, Iowa's coach from 1986-99, is in his first season at Drake and was greeted warmly when he walked onto the court. About a dozen photographers and TV cameramen awaited his arrival and followed him down the floor as he hugged Iowa coach Steve Alford and assistant Rich Walker and shook hands with workers at the scorer's table. Alford presented Davis with a ball in recognition of Davis' 269 victories with the Hawkeyes, the most for any coach at the school. Davis has put together a scrappy team, but the Bulldogs could not keep up with the taller Hawkeyes after playing a strong first half. Trailing just 36-32 at halftime, Drake scored only nine points in the first 11½ minutes of the second half and Iowa built a 61-41 lead. Jeff Horner's 3-pointer capped a 10-2 run that stretched the lead to 46-34. Brunner, Pierce and Reiner all scored as Iowa ran off six straight points for a 54-38 lead, and Pierce's breakaway layup finished a 7-0 run that took the lead to 20. The Hawkeyes led by as many as 25 down the stretch. Drake gave Iowa occasional problems with its press, forcing 12 first-half turnovers, but the Hawkeyes also beat the pressure for several layups. Aside from four 3-pointers, all of Iowa's baskets came on layups, putbacks or short shots in the lane. Iowa finished with 23 turnovers, nine by Pierce. Nate Richie led Drake with 12 points, all on 3-point baskets. The Bulldogs shot just 31.6 percent.
